I'm a halfling druid (starting char of 50) and I'm wondering how important char is for using charm spells...

Until recently I'd never tried charming before, but I've had lots of fun the last few days sending griffons in to fight poachers in Jaggedpine.  The only problem is my charms have a habit of breaking after a minute or two.  Is it worth it to drop 30 wis to add 60 or 80 char?  (my base wis is about 210 and my char is 43 - eye of griffon...:-))

